FBIS4-64216 "drweu084__a94012" FBIS-WEU-94-084-A Daily Report 2 May 1994 ANNEX Germany Kozyrev Proposes Western-Russian Conference on Bosnia Kozyrev Proposes Western-Russian Conference on Bosnia AU2804135494 Hamburg DPA in German 1315 GMT 28 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2804135494 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] Bonn -- At a Western-Russian foreign ministers' conference a general cease-fire should be agreed with the Bosnian parties to the conflict, and the path for a political solution should be cleared. This was proposed by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev today after talks with his German counterpart Klaus Kinkel. No date has yet been set for the foreign ministers' conference. During his exchange of views with Kinkel, Kozyrev stated that a military intervention should only be the very last resort. The Serbs should know that there is a limit that must not be exceeded. Kozyrev mentioned the shelling of the hospital in Gorazde in this respect.
